%N A379508 Sum of the legs of the unique primitive Pythagorean triple (x,y,z) such that (x-y+z)/2 is A002315(n) and such that its long leg and its hypotenuse are consecutive natural numbers.
%H A379508 Andrew Howroyd, <a href="/A379508/b379508.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..200</a>
%H A379508 Miguel-Ángel Pérez García-Ortega, José Manuel Sánchez Muñoz and José Miguel Blanco Casado, <a href="/A379508/a379508.pdf">El Libro de las Ternas Pitagóricas</a>, preprint, 2024.
%H A379508 <a href="/index/Rec#order_03">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (35,-35,1).
%F A379508 a(n) = A362545(n) + A377726(n).
%F A379508 a(n) = 2*A002315(n)^2 - 1.
%F A379508 G.f.: (1 + 62*x + x^2)/((1 - x)*(1 - 34*x + x^2)). - _Andrew Howroyd_, Nov 17 2025
%e A379508 For n=1, the short leg is A362545(1) = 13 and the long leg is A377726(1) = 84 so the sum of the legs is then a(1) = 13 + 84 = 97.
%t A379508 s[n_]:=s[n]=Module[{ra},ra=((1+Sqrt[2])^(2n+1)-(Sqrt[2]-1)^(2n+1))/2;{2ra^2-1}];sumas={};Do[sumas=Join[semis,FullSimplify[s[n]]],{n,0,17}];sumas
